That this is almost not an exaggeration

57
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:06,101
Every console has different requirements

58
00:04:06,162 --> 00:04:08,583
They're each vague and confusing in their own ways

59
00:04:09,084 --> 00:04:15,068
And they kind of require a specialized skill set in order to be certified properly work the way that they're all supposed to that's the inherent

60
00:04:15,108 --> 00:04:16,189
promise behind a console

61
00:04:16,769 --> 00:04:22,071
Large publishers maintain dedicated teams devoted to just getting through the technical requirements

62
00:04:23,011 --> 00:04:29,394
in part because they can and it's good business, but also because you can incur severe financial penalties

63
00:04:29,434 --> 00:04:33,775
and we are talking about like low five figures every time you screw up after your free try

64
00:04:33,855 --> 00:04:38,076
which to a publisher is, somebody's gonna get yelled at into a university, it's like, how much?

65
00:04:39,157 --> 00:04:42,618
And I know all of these things because my first job in games was actually in QA

66
00:04:42,698 --> 00:04:44,879
so I started at the Vendy Universal Games.

67
00:04:46,828 --> 00:04:48,370
I guess younger and thinner.

